main event: A person observed an unidentified object in the sky over Charles City, Iowa in August 1965.
interesting points: The object appeared to be a planet, changing colors between red, green, blue, and white.
The object split into two parts, with one part moving into the center while the other part disappeared.
The object disappeared completely after this maneuver.
The observer believed the object was not a normal aircraft, as it hovered, moved swiftly, and maneuvered in an unusual way.
The observer had seen similar objects and activity on prior occasions.
sighted object: A multi-colored object that split into two parts
